window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p>Bad boys love bad ideas. It's kind of their thing, isn't it? Ethan's no exception. </p> <p><b>Rule Number Seven - I don't care what you've done before. It doesn't matter. It's about what you want to do now.</b> </p> <p>I'm really bad at being a good girl, aren't I? I blame Ethan. He's corrupting me. It's the perfect excuse, but I'm not sure how much longer I can keep using it. </p> <p>\"I think that's what bad boys do, though,\" I say, playing Devil's Advocate. \"It's in your job description: Be as rude as you can, as often as possible.\" </p> <p>\"Maybe,\" he says. \"How about good girls? What are they supposed to do?\" </p> <p>\"Become corrupted by bad boys,\" I say. \"Haven't you even read the bad boy handbook, Ethan? Gosh!\" </p>"; 
